<p>as if the war really was practically over.</p>
<p>In any case, the wonderful advances we are now making, confirm my suspicion that Germany really is breaking up, &amp; that such diplomatic troubles as these will soon clear up before the certainty of impending collapse which faces her. Naturally she will try to make the best of a bad job, but we, I am sure, will not allow her to dodge one iota of the consequences of her own acts.</p>
<p>It is amusing to read some of the silly letters which are written to the "Times" &amp; "Daily Mail" (particularly to the later) by people who want German towns razed, or else suggest some fanciful scheme for making Germany repair the damage she has done.</p>
